 <item> <title>Departments of Education and Justice Reach Settlement Agreement with Jefferson Parish Public School System Ensuring Equal Access and Non-Discrimination in Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/departments-education-and-justice-reach-settlement-agreement-jefferson-parish-public-school-system-ensuring-equal-access-and-non-discrimination-schools</link>
 <description>WASHINGTON -- The Departments of Education and Justice announced today that they have reached a comprehensive agreement with the Jefferson Parish Public School System in Louisiana (JPPSS) to ensure that all students can enroll in school regardless of their own national origin or immigration status, or that of their parents or guardians.  The agreement also resolves complaints regarding JPP</description>
